long_desc.thetext:
We have set the setting "qx.aspects" to "on", to use the profiler qx.dev.Profile. After we have set "qx.aspects" to "on", we get the following error messages:
qx.core.Init: Catched error on init: Error: Please initialize 'qx.ui.window.Manager' objects using the new keyword! at: ,qx.Class:1623, qx.core.Aspect:82, qx.core.Aspect:82, qx.ui.window.MDesktop:77, qx.ui.window.MDesktop:182 ,qx.ui.window.MDesktop:159, qx.ui.core.Widget:2213, qx.core.Aspect:82, qx.ui.core.Widget:1967
The line 77 of class MDeskTop looks like this: this.setWindowManager(new qx.ui.window.Window.DEFAULT_MANAGER_CLASS());
The DEFAULT_MANAGER_CLASS is defined as follows: statics : { /** {Class} The default window manager class. */ DEFAULT_MANAGER_CLASS : qx.ui.window.Manager },
I have work-arounded this issue by replacing the following line: this.setWindowManager(new qx.ui.window.Window.DEFAULT_MANAGER_CLASS()); with: this.setWindowManager(new qx.ui.window.Manager());
May be the old code needs some kind of "eval".
After I have implemented this work-around, I got the next error message:
qx.ui.core.Widget._createChildControl threw error: Error: Please initialize 'qx.ui.table.headerrenderer.Default' objects using the new keyword! at: , qx.Class:1623 qx.core.Aspect:82 qx.core.Aspect:82 qx.ui.table.columnmodel.Basic:161 qx.core.Aspect:82
The class qx.ui.table.columnmodel.Basic contains a similar code without an eval: var headerRenderer = this.__headerRenderer || (this.__headerRenderer = new qx.ui.table.columnmodel.Basic.DEFAULT_HEADER_RENDERER()); var dataRenderer = this.__dataRenderer || (this.__dataRenderer = new qx.ui.table.columnmodel.Basic.DEFAULT_DATA_RENDERER()); var editorFactory = this.__editorFactory || (this.__editorFactory = new qx.ui.table.columnmodel.Basic.DEFAULT_EDITOR_FACTORY());
The priority of this issue is low, since I have found a work-around.
